
[1]liturgy

   LIT'URGY, n. [Gr. public, and work.

   In a general sense, all public ceremonies that belong to divine
   service; hence, in a restricted sense, among the Romanists, the mass;
   and among protestants, the common prayer, or the formulary of public
   prayers.
